{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","text":"CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"centerOffset","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"title":"centerOffset","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"}}}